Preheat your #oven{} to 240°C/220°C fan/gas mark 9.

Halve the @bell pepper{1} and discard the core and seeds. Slice into thin strips.

Trim the @carrot{1}, then coarsely grate (no need to peel).

Pop the pepper onto a lined #baking tray{}. Toss with @salt{to taste}, @pepper{to taste} and a drizzle of @oil{to taste}.

When the oven is hot, roast on the top shelf until soft and slightly charred, ~{10-12%minutes}.

Meanwhile, place a #pan{} over medium-high heat (without oil).

Once hot, add the @turkey mince{250%grams} and fry until cooked through, ~{6-8%minutes}.

> IMPORTANT: Wash hands and equipment after handling raw mince. Mince is cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

Use a #spoon{} to break the mince up as it cooks. Season with @salt{to taste} and @pepper{to taste}.

Add the @Mexican style spice mix{2%sachets} and @chipotle paste{1%sachet} to the pan and fry until fragrant, ~{2-3%minutes}. Season to taste with salt and pepper.

To make the slaw, mix the grated carrot with the @aioli{1%sachet}.

Pop the @tortilla{8} into the oven to warm, ~{1-2%minutes}.

In a separate #bowl{} for the salad, mix the @red wine vinegar{1%sachet} with @oil{1%tbsp}.

> Double oil amount for 4p.

Just before serving, toss the @salad leaves{40%grams} through the dressing and season with salt and pepper.

Serve the carrot slaw, spiced turkey mince, dressed salad leaves and roasted peppers in separate dishes.

Divide the warmed tortillas between plates.

Allow everyone to assemble their own chipotle turkey tacos at the table.